caption: Table 1: Correctness of solutions for different algorithms.
description: This table presents the number of correct solutions obtained by ASAp and GCD for various benchmarks across different structured prediction tasks.  It compares the performance of the two algorithms in terms of generating grammatically correct outputs that satisfy given constraints. The benchmarks include different variations of string manipulation tasks (SLIA) and bit-vector arithmetic problems (INV-BV).  Higher numbers indicate better performance.

caption: Table 1: Correctness of solutions for different algorithms.
description: This table presents the number of correct solutions obtained by both ASAp and GCD algorithms across various benchmarks.  A higher number indicates better performance.  The benchmarks encompass different types of problems, including those involving string manipulation (SLIA) and bit-vector arithmetic (INV-BV). The data reveals that while both methods often generate correct solutions, ASAp's performance varies across different benchmark tasks.  In some cases, ASAp yields significantly more correct solutions, while in others, GCD outperforms ASAp.
